{"title":"Last chance to get tickets for Cyclist Track Days in London","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-london-2025","date":1747070935000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-london-2025\">Last chance to get tickets for Cyclist Track Days in London</a></p>\n\n<p>The second Cyclist Track Days event of the year is taking place at London’s Lee Valley VeloPark this Saturday 17th May, and there aren’t many spots left.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether you are in the market for a new bike or just want to try out some of the best bikes in the world, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">Cyclist Track Days</a> offer a unique experience to test the latest top-end bikes from the leading names on the market. All brands will also have ambassadors on site who can advise you on the models and discuss all things cycling.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2025 brand lineup features Trek and Specialized (courtesy of Balfe’s Bikes), along with Basso, Cannondale, Condor, Enve, Factor, Giant/Liv, Orbea, Ribble, Scott, Van Rysel, Wilier and Dolan.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out all the bikes <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikes-cyclist-track-days-2025\">here</a>, although missing from this list is the world’s newest bike, the brand new Cannondale Synapse, which will also be available to test ride on Saturday.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So if you want to spend the day riding amazing bikes in the sunshine – with lunch and coffee thrown in – don’t miss out.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/cc/cyclist-track-days-2025-3855053\" target=\"_blank\">BOOK YOUR TICKET HERE</a></strong></h2>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n       